HEADWORD: Bordlode
<hw>Bord"lode`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Bordar</ets> (or perh. <ets>bord</ets> a board) +
<ets>lode</ets> leading.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>The
service formerly required of a tenant, to carry timber from the woods to
the lord's house.</def> <rj><au>Bailey. Mozley & W.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

